import numpy as np

#  
x = np.arange(-5, 5, 0.1)
y1 = x**2 -2
y2 = 20*np.cos(x)**2 # NumPy cos() np.cos() 

plt.figure(1) # 1   
plt.plot(x, y1) #     

plt.figure(2) # 2   
plt.plot(x, y2) #     

plt.figure(1) #   1   
plt.plot(x, y2) #     

plt.figure(2) #   2   
plt.clf() # 2      
plt.plot(x, y1) #     

plt.show()

In [15]:
import numpy as np

#  
x = np.arange(0, 10, 0.1)
y1 = 0.3*(x-5)**2 + 1
y2 = -1.5*x + 3
y3 = np.sin(x)**2 # NumPy sin() np.sin() 
y4 = 10*np.exp(-x) + 1 # NumPy exp() np.exp() 

# 2  2     p   
plt.subplot(2,2,1) # p 1
plt.plot(x,y1)

plt.subplot(2,2,2) # p 2
plt.plot(x,y2)

plt.subplot(2,2,3) # p 3
plt.plot(x,y3)

plt.subplot(2,2,4) # p 4
plt.plot(x,y4)

plt.show()

In [36]:
import numpy as np

city = ['', '', '', '', '', '', '']

# (latitude) (longitude)
lat  = [37.56, 37.45, 36.35, 35.87, 35.53, 35.18, 35.16] 
lon = [126.97, 126.70, 127.38, 128.60, 129.31, 129.07, 126.85]

#  (/km^2): 2017  
pop_den = [16154, 2751, 2839, 2790, 1099, 4454, 2995]

size = np.array(pop_den) * 0.2 #    
colors = ['r', 'g', 'b', 'c', 'm', 'k', 'y'] #   

plt.scatter(lon, lat, s=size, c=colors, alpha=0.5)
plt.xlabel('(longitude)')
plt.ylabel('(latitude)')
plt.title('  (2017)')

for x, y, name in zip(lon, lat, city):
    x -= 0.09
    y -= 0.03
    plt.text(x, y, name) #      

plt.show()

In [38]:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np

n_data = len(member_IDs)     #       4
index = np.arange(n_data)   # NumPy    (0, 1, 2, 3)
plt.bar(index, before_ex)   # bar(x,y) x=index, height=before_ex  
plt.show()

plt.show()

plt.show()

plt.show()
In [42]:

plt.show()
In [43]:

plt.bar(index + barWidth, after_ex , color='m', align='edge', width = barWidth, label='after')

plt.xticks(index + barWidth, member_IDs)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

x = np.arange(0, 5, 1)
y1 = x
y2 = x + 1
y3 = x + 2
y4 = x + 3

plt.plot(x, y1, x, y2, x, y3, x, y4)

plt.grid(True)
plt.xlabel('x')
plt.ylabel('y')
plt.title('Saving a figure')

#    . dpi 100

plt.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
